3.title: Looking Classy! Daily Makeup
3.plot: Hello, this is Ssong Yang. I filmed this video to try out Etude products that I received as gifts. Some of you thought this was sponsored. I revised it. :-)\nThank you for watching my video. Hope it can be a help to you all. Play 101 Stick Primer: This felt sticky like a glue. The texture may help the color to be more vibrant, but I'm not sure if it helps for a matt and smooth base. Play 101 #09 Sand Highlighter: Personally, I was really looking forward to this because of the color, but in the end, I really wasn't into this.

8.title: Autumn Photogenic Goddess Makeup
8.plot: Hi, guys. this is SSong Yang. :) Today, I bring you a photogenic goddess makeup. Whenever I see photos of female ulzzangs (a South Korean term meaning \"best face\" or \"good-looking\" = god or goddess online), I always think their makeup looks too heavy to do on a daily basis even though it looks good in photos. So I did that kind of makeup today lol. Doesn't mean that I'm an ulzzang. I'm doing an ulzzang makeup.

9.title: Glamorous & Unique Halloween Makeup Tutorial
9.plot: At last. Halloween has come. As well as a stye in my eye - :-) So I will show you guys a Halloween eye makeup only :( However. I used makeup products ONLY so it would be easy for you guys to try out.

10.title: Whatever Makeup That I Wanted to Do (Ft. Too Faced Peach Palette)
10.plot: Hi, I'm back with dark hair. I don't even remember when was the last time I had dark hair. Maybe a bright color is better? Anyways, now I like this color better. Hye-nam from A By Bom always does my hair.
